`φs` and `φs'` lists of `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp` in `WickAlgebra 𝓕` the following\nrelation holds:\n\n`superCommute φs φs' = φs * φs' - 𝓢(φs, φs') • φs' * φs`\n\nThe notation `[a, b]ₛ` is used for `superCommute a b`.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickAlgebra/SuperCommute.html#FieldSpecification.WickAlgebra.superCommute","kind":"def","line":90,"name":"FieldSpecification.WickAlgebra.superCommute","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L90-L122"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickAlgebra/SuperCommute.html#FieldSpecification.WickAlgebra.superCommuteRight_eq_of_equiv\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">WickAlgebra</span>.<span class=\"name\">superCommuteRight_eq_of_equiv</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a1 </span><span class=\"fn\">a2</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldOpFreeAlgebra/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOpFreeAlgebra\">FieldOpFreeAlgebra</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\">a1</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#HasEquiv.Equiv\">≈</a> <span class=\"fn\">a2</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickAlgebra/SuperCommute.html#FieldSpecification.WickAlgebra.superCommuteRight\">superCommuteRight</a> <span class=\"fn\">a1</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/Pe